The course was unfortunately slow and repetitive. Many of the videos could have been far more concise and the points were repeated over and over. The last week had interesting points to it but for the most part the whole course could have been done in two equivalent weeks. Rape and sexual trauma was skimmed and trotted around and the course would have been better if it made a point of not speaking about it altogether due to its different nature from other traumas mentioned. Good try but I felt I was forcing myself to watch the videos as there was so little to absorb from them that was not already evident as a self aware human.
A very monotonous way of presenting the material.
testing does not give enough feedback to learn correct answers

En general no me gustó mucho. Quería saber cosas más prácticas que me sirvieran con mis pacientes o con niños con los que vaya a trabajar. Pero se enfoca más en mostrar estudios y ejemplos de niños que han vivido traumas. No es muy práctico, y está enfocado para personas que vayan a hacer programas a niveles más grandes, en comunidades con niños que han vivido tramas, o para colegios con niños. No me sirvió mucho como profesional de la salud que trabaja con niños.
Great course and very relevant to our day and age. I just wish that videos were more updated and so were the readings/ resources. I felt that videos are relevant however very old.
I definitively enjoyed it, but I felt it was less relevant to a third work context than I had hoped. If this does not bother you, I recommend it!

Overall, the course has been educational and useful.  However, being dated back to 2010, the course needs further thorough revision with regards to the content, presentation style (very old-fashioned videos with the boring slides), home assignments with no feedback, no applicable resources that can be used instantly in the classroom or teacher trainings.  Thank you for the opportunity to learn more about resilience!

Quizzes are kind of confusing, and Id like more assignments to count for grades and less quizzes. Like points for discussions.  Or give examples in own life of when you personally had to use resilience.

This course gives great insight and a good overview of resilience in children and the current place we are in, in terms of research in this field. I would recommend this to anyone who interacts with children and people in general because a big lesson that came from this course is that it is never to late to show resilience. It has given me a good footing on some of the principles and I look forward to implementing what I learnt in my life and work.
The course gave an excellent overview on resilience. Prof Masten is a very good presenter and moved at exactly the right pace.
It was an excellent course in case of resilience in children. A sensitive topic which has been described nicely with lots of case studies and example.
It's good that there are a variety of subtopics per week. However, sometimes some videos are not specific, i.e. sometimes they are more extensive than they could be.

I really enjoy and learned a lot about resilience in this course. Profesor Masten is a well known researcher in this field and know what she is talking. I believe it is a good appetizer for those who aren't sure about what way to go within the psychology, psychiatry, and mental health sciences. I would have loved for this course to have talked more in detail about the treatment and therapies to treat children and how to actually do the treatment; some therapies are mention during the course, but it doesn't really emphasises on any of them.  Another reason that I rate this course 4 starts is because I posted a couple of questions about the videos of the course and they were never answered, I felt like if nobody was on the other side. I appreciate your input. Thank you!

I found this course extremely informative.  The thorough overview provided of the research that has gone into the science of resilience was fascinating.  The concept of adaptive factors and promotive factors for improving ones ability to overcome adversity was valuable because I work with at-risk students. I appreciated the perspectives offered by the guest speakers included in the course as well.  However, the discussion forum was only slightly useful and having to take a "final" exam was unnecessary.  I found the final exam process infuriating, especially when the questions changed for every retake not providing the option for the process of elimination. Since it's not a course one is getting credit for or to receive a final grade for a college transcript, it shouldn't be an additional requirement for completing a course!

I thought the course was very interesting and also very varied in terms of the content presented. I liked being able to follow the links and learn on my own terms the different types of strategies and interventions that are being put into place. Dr. Masten provides lots of insight into the current research and was able to give us an insight into the research by talking to other influential people in the field which was very cool! I do think that sometimes the coursework was a bit much for my schedule especially with some of the required readings but it was nevertheless manageable given the right schedule of self-discipline.

It was an excellent course. A great overview of knowledge that is very needed. I believe it needs some updating and some more energy. Sometimes I found the lectures hard to follow as it was lacking energetic engagement.
I felt that at many points, the course focused on bluntly conveying facts more than making the videos engaging. There should be more interesting interactions.
I enjoyed the course, but it needed more depth, possibly in treatments and outcomes.  The lectures were kind of long and windy, but informative.
Lots of material. Good instructor. But the course was tad too long. 4 weeks would be ideal
Very Well organized.

The course covers the subject very systematically from the inception of the study of resilience up to the recent advances. The suggested videos are very carefully chosen and give a lot of food for thought.  The quiz questions reinforce the concepts learned in the lectures. It is especially useful to have the checklist quiz where one marks all the items that one has completed e.g. filling surveys, joining discussions etc.This course has been very helpful to me. Thankyou for the effort that must have gone into making it.
